        <exercise xml:id="ex-equilateral-garden">
            <statement>
                <p>
                    A gardener is designing an equilateral triangular flower bed with each side measuring <m>6\,\text{m}</m>.
                    Give all answers in exact form.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li><p>Use trigonometry to find the exact height of the triangular bed.</p></li>
                        <li><p>Find the exact area of the flower bed.</p></li>
                        <li><p>Find the exact radius of a circular fountain that could be inscribed in the triangular bed (touching all three sides).</p></li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
                <image width="45%">
                <latex-image label="exercise-equilateral-garden">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                        % Equilateral triangle
                        \draw[very thick, fill=green!20] (0,0) -- (4,0) -- (2,3.464) -- cycle;
                        % Height
                        \draw[thick, dashed, blue] (2,0) -- (2,3.464);
                        % Inscribed circle
                        \draw[thick, cyan] (2,1.155) circle (1.155);
                        % Center
                        \fill (2,1.155) circle (0.06);
                        % Radius
                        \draw[thick, red] (2,1.155) -- (2,0);
                        % Labels
                        \node[below] at (2,0) {$6\,\text{m}$};
                        \node[left, blue] at (1.9,1.8) {$h$};
                        \node[right, red] at (2.1,0.5) {$r$};
                        % Angle
                        \draw (0.5,0) arc[start angle=0, end angle=60, radius=0.5cm];
                        \node at (0.85,0.35) {$60^\circ$};
                        % Right angle
                        \draw (2,0.25) -- (2.25,0.25) -- (2.25,0);
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
                </image>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>Using half the base (3 m) and the <m>60^\circ</m> angle:</p>
                            <p><m>h = 3 \times \tan\,60^\circ = 3 \times \sqrt{3} = 3\sqrt{3}\,\text{m}</m> (exact)</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Area = <m>\frac{1}{2} \times \text{base} \times \text{height} = \frac{1}{2} \times 6 \times 3\sqrt{3} = 9\sqrt{3}\,\text{m}^2</m> (exact)</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>The inscribed circle radius <m>r = \frac{\text{Area}}{s}</m> where <m>s</m> is the semi-perimeter:</p>
                            <p><m>s = \frac{6 + 6 + 6}{2} = 9\,\text{m}</m></p>
                            <p><m>r = \frac{9\sqrt{3}}{9} = \sqrt{3}\,\text{m}</m> (exact)</p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
                <p>
                    The exact answers are: height <m>= 3\sqrt{3}\,\text{m}</m>, area <m>= 9\sqrt{3}\,\text{m}^2</m>, radius <m>= \sqrt{3}\,\text{m}</m>.
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

                <exercise xml:id="ex-airplane-altitude">
            <statement>
                <p>
                    An airplane is flying at a constant altitude. A person on the ground observes the airplane 
                    at an angle of elevation of <m>50^\circ</m>. After the airplane has flown <m>500\,\text{m}</m> 
                    directly toward the person, the angle of elevation becomes <m>70^\circ</m>. 
                    Find the altitude of the airplane.
                </p>
                <image width="65%">
                <latex-image label="exercise-airplane-altitude">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                        % Ground line
                        \draw[very thick] (-0.5,0) -- (8,0);
                        % Person
                        \draw[thick] (0.5,0) -- (0.5,0.6);
                        \draw[thick, fill=cyan] (0.5,0.72) circle (0.12);
                        % First airplane position (box)
                        \draw[thick, fill=gray] (6.8,4.8) rectangle (7.8,5.2);
                        \node[below] at (7.3,4.7) {Position 1};
                        % Second airplane position (box, closer)
                        \draw[thick, fill=gray] (3.3,4.8) rectangle (4.3,5.2);
                        \node[below] at (3.8,4.7) {Position 2};
                        % Altitude line
                        \draw[dashed] (7,0) -- (7,5);
                        \draw[dashed] (3.5,0) -- (3.5,5);
                        % Lines of sight
                        \draw[very thick, dashed, blue] (0.5,0) -- (7,5);
                        \draw[very thick, dashed, red] (0.5,0) -- (3.5,5);
                        % Angles
                        \draw (1.5,0) arc[start angle=0, end angle=35, radius=1cm];
                        \node at (2,0.35) {$50^\circ$};
                        \draw (1.2,0) arc[start angle=0, end angle=55, radius=0.7cm];
                        \node at (1.3,0.7) {$70^\circ$};
                        % Distance between positions
                        \draw[&lt;-&gt;, thick] (3.5,5.5) -- (7,5.5);
                        \node[above] at (5.25,5.5) {$500\,\text{m}$};
                        % Altitude label
                        \node[right] at (7.1,2.5) {$h = ?$};
                        % Right angles
                        \draw (6.7,0) -- (6.7,0.3) -- (7,0.3);
                        \draw (3.2,0) -- (3.2,0.3) -- (3.5,0.3);
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
                </image>
            </statement>
            <hint>
                <p>
                    Let the horizontal distance from the person to position 2 be <m>x</m>. 
                    Then the distance to position 1 is <m>x + 500</m>. 
                    Use <m>\tan\,70^\circ = \frac{h}{x}</m> and <m>\tan\,50^\circ = \frac{h}{x+500}</m>.
                </p>
            </hint>
            <answer>
                <image width="65%">
                <latex-image label="exercise-airplane-altitude-answer">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                        % Ground line
                        \draw[very thick] (-0.5,0) -- (8.5,0);
                        % Person
                        \draw[thick] (0.5,0) -- (0.5,0.6);
                        \draw[thick, fill=cyan] (0.5,0.72) circle (0.12);
                        \node[below] at (0.5,-0.1) {Observer};
                        % First airplane position (box)
                        \draw[thick, fill=gray] (6.8,4.8) rectangle (7.8,5.2);
                        \node[above] at (7.3,5.3) {Position 1};
                        % Second airplane position (box, closer)
                        \draw[thick, fill=gray] (3.3,4.8) rectangle (4.3,5.2);
                        \node[above] at (3.8,5.3) {Position 2};
                        % Altitude lines
                        \draw[dashed, thick] (7.3,0) -- (7.3,4.8);
                        \draw[dashed, thick] (3.8,0) -- (3.8,4.8);
                        % Horizontal flight path
                        \draw[dashed, thick] (0.5,5) -- (8,5);
                        % Lines of sight
                        \draw[very thick, blue] (0.5,0) -- (7.3,5);
                        \draw[very thick, red] (0.5,0) -- (3.8,5);
                        % Angles
                        \draw[thick] (1.8,0) arc[start angle=0, end angle=36.5, radius=1.3cm];
                        \node at (2.4,0.4) {$50^\circ$};
                        \draw[thick] (1.3,0) arc[start angle=0, end angle=56.5, radius=0.8cm];
                        \node at (1.2,0.7) {$70^\circ$};
                        % Distance between positions (500 m)
                        \draw[&lt;-&gt;, thick, purple] (3.8,5.6) -- (7.3,5.6);
                        \node[above, purple] at (5.55,5.6) {$500\,\text{m}$};
                        % Altitude label h
                        \draw[&lt;-&gt;, thick, green!50!black] (7.8,0) -- (7.8,4.8);
                        \node[right, green!50!black] at (7.9,2.4) {$h$};
                        % Distance x (from observer to position 2)
                        \draw[&lt;-&gt;, thick, orange] (0.5,-0.5) -- (3.8,-0.5);
                        \node[below, orange] at (2.15,-0.5) {$x$};
                        % Distance x + 500 (from observer to position 1)
                        \draw[&lt;-&gt;, thick, blue!70!black] (0.5,-1.1) -- (7.3,-1.1);
                        \node[below, blue!70!black] at (3.9,-1.1) {$x + 500$};
                        % Right angles
                        \draw (7,0) -- (7,0.3) -- (7.3,0.3);
                        \draw (3.5,0) -- (3.5,0.3) -- (3.8,0.3);
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
                </image>
                <p>
                    From <m>\tan\,70^\circ = \frac{h}{x}</m>, we get <m>h = x\tan\,70^\circ</m>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    From <m>\tan\,50^\circ = \frac{h}{x+500}</m>, we get <m>h = (x+500)\tan\,50^\circ</m>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Equating: <m>x\tan\,70^\circ = (x+500)\tan\,50^\circ</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>x(2.747) = (x+500)(1.192)</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>2.747x = 1.192x + 596</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>1.555x = 596</m>, so <m>x = 383.3\,\text{m}</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Therefore: <m>h = 383.3 \times \tan\,70^\circ = 383.3 \times 2.747 = 1053\,\text{m}</m>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>
